K Nearest Neighbors => classifies data points based on similarities. 
it analysis the similarities between the new data pt and earlier data pts 
and puts the new case into the category that is most similar to the already 
available cases. 

lets say two categories in the dataset 
category 1 and category 2 
new datapoint is presented in the dataset 
how do we classify this new data point?? 
knn helps us assign new datapt to a specific category. 


KNN Algorithm 
Step 1 => Choose the number of K of neighbors. 
Step 2 => Take the K nearest neighbors of the new data pt according to the euclidean distance or 
other distance. 
Step 3 => Among the k neighbors, count the number of data pts in each category. 
Step 4 => Assign the new data pt to the category where u counted the most neighbors. 

How to find the nearest neighbors ?? Using euclidean distance 
formula => distance between P1 and P2 = root of (x2 - x1) pow 2 + (y2 - y1) pow 2 
look at the data pt in specific category that is closest to the new data pt and 
add new data pt to that category. 